#define CS_APP_MISCOMPARE_ERR_EID   30

'Checksum Failure: Application %s, Expected: 0x%08X, Calculated: 0x%08X'

Event Message:
'Checksum Failure: Application %s, Expected: 0x%08X, Calculated: 0x%08X'
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when a checksum miscompare occurs when checksumming entries in the table of applications to checksum.

The Application field is the name of the app.
The Expected field is the checksum value that was expected to be calculated.
The Calculated field is the new value that was calculated.
